# OpenV Master Skill

## Environment Configuration
**Docker Image:** `crpi-5901rc39czlvlzc5.cn-beijing.personal.cr.aliyuncs.com/open-v/openv-dev:amd64-latest`
**Python Venv:** `/opt/asic_env`
**Workspace:** `/workspace`

## Capabilities Overview
I can assist you with the following ASIC/FPGA workflows. If your request matches one of these, I will use the specialized skill:

* **Linting & Formatting**: (`lint.md`) for Verible/Verilator checks.
* **Simulation**: (`cocotb-test.md`) for verifying design with Python/CocoTB.
* **Synthesis**: (`synthesis.md`) for Yosys synthesis and OpenSTA timing.
* **Management**: (`run-container.md`) for starting/stopping the Docker container.
* **Maintenance**: (`build-image.md`) for updating the Docker image itself.

## Common "One-Shot" Commands
If you need to run a quick generic command inside the environment without a specific workflow:

```bash
docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/workspace [crpi-5901rc39czlvlzc5.cn-beijing.personal.cr.aliyuncs.com/open-v/openv-dev:amd64-latest](https://crpi-5901rc39czlvlzc5.cn-beijing.personal.cr.aliyuncs.com/open-v/openv-dev:amd64-latest) bash -c 'source /opt/asic_env/bin/activate && <YOUR_COMMAND_HERE>'

Project Scaffolding

If asked to "Initialize a new OpenV project", create this structure:

    src/ (Source files)

    test/ (CocoTB tests)

    Makefile (See cocotb-test.md for template)

    config.tcl (For synthesis)